{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17626066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17626066"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:33:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:33:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17052"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17052","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17052"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.33,0,0.58,0,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9742"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74913"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9742"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17052"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60411"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5092"},{"type":"tags","id":"5294"},{"type":"tags","id":"5296"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22920"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23099"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74913","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74913"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMethotrexate is a commonly prescribed disease-modifying antirheumatic drug (DMARD) used to treat various autoimmune conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate supplementation required with methotrexate therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Daily folinic acid supplementation","Daily iron supplementation","Weekly folic acid supplementation","Daily calcium supplementation","Weekly vitamin B12 supplementation"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct supplementation with methotrexate therapy is \u003Cstrong\u003Eweekly folic acid supplementation \u003C/strong\u003Egiven 24 hours after methotrexate. This timing (dose given 24 hours after methotrexate) allows methotrexate to exert its therapeutic effect while reducing side effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile\u003Cstrong\u003E daily calcium supplementation \u003C/strong\u003Eis important for bone health, calcium is not specifically required with methotrexate therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDaily iron supplementation\u003C/strong\u003E is not routinely required with methotrexate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeekly vitamin B12 supplementation\u003C/strong\u003E is also incorrect, as vitamin B12 is not specifically required with methotrexate therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDaily folinic acid (leucovorin) supplementation\u003C/strong\u003E is used in methotrexate toxicity or high-dose therapy, not routine supplementation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFolic acid supplementation helps prevent common methotrexate side effects including gastrointestinal upset, mucositis, and bone marrow suppression. The 24-hour delay after methotrexate administration prevents interference with its therapeutic antifolate effect.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Treatment with methotrexate should be coupled with concurrent folic acid supplementation to reduce side effects while maintaining therapeutic efficacy.","Folic acid should be given 24 hours after a methotrexate dose to avoid reducing its the medication\u0027s therapeutic effect.","Folic acid supplementation reduces the risk of gastrointestinal side effects, mucositis, and bone marrow suppression from methotrexate."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/","Parker S, Hanrahan P, Barrett C. Folate for therapy. Aust Prescr 2013;36:52-5. https://doi.org/10.18773/austprescr.2013.024"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60411"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17052"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60411","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60411"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T10:00:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T14:05:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9742"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74913"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"